Durban - Police are still searching for the suspects who shot dead a passenger in a taxi on Friday near Cornubia. According to police spokesperson Captain Nqobile Gwala the victim was travelling in a taxi on the R102 Main Road at around 12:25pm when two occupants in the Toyota Camry stopped the taxi. "They opened the door and the victim attempted to flee the scene. The suspects fired shots at him in the head. He was declared dead at the scene by paramedics," said Gwala. A case of murder is being investigated by Verulam SAPS. According to Prem Balram, director of Reaction Unit South Africa, their control room received multiple calls from passing motorists who witnessed a gold Toyota Camry force the Mercedes Benz to stop. "Several armed men then pulled the passenger out of the vehicle and fire rounds at him." The unknown male was shot once at the back of his head with the bullet exiting the right side of his forehead. Daily News